columns.text:
The **spot rate** is the *exchange rate in a spot trade*. The **spot trade** is an agreement to exchange currencies based on the exchange rate on that date and must be settled within two business days.
&nbsp;

A **forward trade** is an agreement to *exchange currency in the future*. The *exchange rate in the agreement* of a forward trade is called a **forward exchange rate.**

First, we will determine the cost of the project in dollars.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cost of the Project in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cost of the project in € }}{\text{Spot Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{ € 2,000,000}}{\text{ € 0.5}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 4,000,000}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cost of the project is worth **$ 4,000,000**.

Next, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 1.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000}}{\text{€ 0.51}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,764,706}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 1 when converted into dollars is **$ 1,764,706**.

Next, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 2.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000}}{\text{€ 0.52}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,730,769}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 2 when converted into dollars is **$ 1,730,769**.

Lastly, we will determine the expected cash flow in dollar in year 3.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Cash Flow in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{Exchange Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000}}{\text{€ 0.53}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,698,113}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The cash flow in Year 3 when converted into dollars is **$ 1,698,113**.

First, we will get the present value of Year 1:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,764,706 }}{\text{1 +.10 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,764,706 }}{\text{1.10 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,764,706 }}{\text{1.10 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,604,278}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 1 is **$ 1,604,278**.

Next, we will get the present value of Year 2:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,730,769 }}{\text{1 +.10 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,730,769 }}{\text{1.10 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,730,769}}{\text{1.21 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,430,388}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **$ 1,430,388**.

Lastly, we will get the present value of Year 3:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in \$ }}{\text{(1 + Discount Rate)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,698,113 }}{\text{1 +.10 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,698,113 }}{\text{1.10 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{\$ 1,698,113}}{\text{1.331 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 1,275,817}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 3 is **$ 1,275,817**.

Applying the formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{$R_{Fc}$} &=\text{$R_{US}$}-\text{$h_{US}$}+\text{$h_{FC}$}\\
&=\text{0.10}-\text{0.05}+\text{0.07}\\

&=\boxed{\text{12 \%}}
\end{aligned}$$

&nbsp;

The required return in Euros is **12%**

Next, we will determine the NPV in Euros. We need to determine the present value of the cash inflow after 3 years. First, we will compute the present value in Year 1.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12}^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12 }^1}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{€ 803,571}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 1 is **€ 803,571**.

Next, we will compute the present value in Year 2.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12}^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12 }^2}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.2544 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{€ 717,474}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 2 is **€ 717,474**.

Lastly, we will compute the present value in Year 3.
$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present Value } &= \dfrac{\text{Cash Flow in € }}{\text{(1+Required Return)}^t}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12}^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.12 }^3}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 900,000 }}{\text{1.4049 }}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{€ 640,602}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The present value in Year 3 is **€ 640,602**.

Now that we have determined the NPV in euros, we will now convert it into U.S. dollars.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{NPV in \$} &= \dfrac{\text{NPV in € }}{\text{Spot Rate}}\\[15pt]
&= \dfrac{\text{€ 161,647 }}{\text{€ 0.5}}\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\text{\$ 323,294}}
\end{aligned}$$
&nbsp;

The NPV in dollars is **$ 323,294**.
